EXPLANATION – Matter in bolded italics is new; matter between brackets [omitted material] is material to be omitted.
AN ACT relating to forestry; revising provisions relating to logging
permits; removing certain requirements relating to a
cutting operation; and providing other matters properly
relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Under existing law, a timber owner or the agent of a timber owner is required
2 to secure a logging permit from the State Forester Firewarden prior to any logging
3 or cutting operation. (NRS 528.042) Existing law defines the term “logging
4 operation” as the commercial harvesting of trees by a timber owner or the agent of
5 a timber owner using certain methods. (NRS 528.0175) Section 1 of this bill
6 removes the requirement to secure a logging permit for a cutting operation.
7 Existing law requires every timber owner or operator to sow suitable grass seed
8 on certain trails, roads and landings upon completion of a logging or cutting
9 operation. (NRS 528.057) Existing law also requires the holder of a timberland
10 conversion certificate to provide a copy of the certificate to any timber operator
11 prior to any logging or cutting operation on land covered by the certificate. (NRS
12 528.086) Sections 1.3 and 1.7 of this bill remove such requirements for a cutting
13 operation.
