THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF NEVADA, REPRESENTED IN
SENATE AND ASSEMBLY, DO ENACT AS FOLLOWS:
1 Section 1. NRS 528.042 is hereby amended to read as follows:
2 528.042 1. Prior to any logging [or cutting] operation, any
3 timber owner or the agent of the timber owner shall secure a logging
4 permit from the State Forester Firewarden.
5 2. Application for such permit shall be made to the nearest
6 office of the Division of Forestry of the State Department of
7 Conservation and Natural Resources.
8 Sec. 1.3. NRS 528.057 is hereby amended to read as follows:
9 528.057 1. Every timber owner or operator, upon completion
10 of his or her logging [or cutting] operation, shall sow suitable grass
11 seed on skid trails, skid roads, unmaintained roads and landings to
12 help maintain the productive condition of the cut-over timberlands.
13 Drill seedings shall be done where feasible.
14 2. The seed shall:
15 (a) Be approved by the State Forester Firewarden;
16 (b) Not be sown during windy weather or when the ground is
17 frozen or under any other unsuitable conditions; and
18 (c) Be spread evenly at not less than 12 pounds per acre when
19 moisture conditions are favorable.
20 Sec. 1.7. NRS 528.086 is hereby amended to read as follows:
21 528.086 Prior to any logging [or cutting] operation on any land
22 covered by a timberland conversion certificate, the holder shall
23 furnish a copy of such certificate to any timber operator harvesting
24 forest products on such land.
25 Sec. 2. This act becomes effective on July 1, 2025.
